fields.title: HOLLY
fields.author: by Stephen King
fields.description: The private detective Holly Gibney investigates whether a married pair of octogenarian academics had anything to do with Bonnie Dahl’s disappearance.

fields.title: THINGS WE LEFT BEHIND
fields.author: by Lucy Score
fields.description: The third book in the Knockemout series. A mogul and a small-town librarian share a dark secret from their past.

fields.title: PAYBACK IN DEATH
fields.author: by J.D. Robb
fields.description: The 57th book of the In Death series. Eve Dallas looks into the death of an internal affairs captain.

fields.title: FOURTH WING
fields.author: by Rebecca Yarros
fields.description: Violet Sorrengail is urged by the commanding general, who also is her mother, to become a candidate for the elite dragon riders.

fields.title: THE RIVER WE REMEMBER
fields.author: by William Kent Krueger
fields.description: Suspicions and accusations complicate a sheriff’s investigation of a wealthy landowner’s murder in a small Minnesota town in 1958.

fields.title: TOM LAKE
fields.author: by Ann Patchett
fields.description: Three daughters, who return to their family orchard in the spring of 2020, learn about their mother’s relationship with a famous actor.

fields.title: THE LONGMIRE DEFENSE
fields.author: by Craig Johnson
fields.description: The 19th book in the Longmire series. A rifle connected to a cold case once belonged to Walt’s grandfather.

fields.title: TOM CLANCY: WEAPONS GRADE
fields.author: by Don Bentley
fields.description: Jack Ryan Jr. witnesses a professional hit and gets caught up in the cold case of a college student who vanished.

fields.title: THE HOUSEMAID
fields.author: by Freida McFadden
fields.description: Troubles surface when a woman looking to make a fresh start takes a job in the home of the Winchesters.

fields.title: ASSISTANT TO THE VILLAIN
fields.author: by Hannah Nicole Maehrer
fields.description: Evie Sage gets a job doing unspecified office duties for the most infamous villain in the kingdom of Rennedawn.
